The paper addresses the problem of one-shot imitation learning, which involves learning to execute a previously unseen task based on a single demonstration. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper proposes a novel formulation of the problem as a symbolic planning problem, which further supports the relevance of the paper to these sub-fields. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.CV, and cs.SY, in that order.
